cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.IT

The paper discusses the vulnerability of wireless avionic systems to attack, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves human pilots interacting with the attacked systems, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The analysis of the impact on the handling of the aircraft involves system engineering (cs.SY), and the implementation of the attacks involves software engineering (cs.SE) and information theory (cs.IT).
